<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,845,1551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
One of us (RLW) examined the 
<typeStatus box="[522,624,845,871]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
(by monotypy), a male measuring 
<quantity box="[1031,1135,845,871]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.23" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="12.3">12.3 mm</quantity>
X 5.0 mm, labeled as follows: “Holo-type [red rimmed circle]/ 
<number box="[601,646,885,911]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="402.0">402</number>
[h]/ Ventanas, Mex., 
<quantity box="[905,989,885,911]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.096" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" unit="ft" value="2000.0">2000ft</quantity>
., Forrer/ 
<taxonomicName box="[1089,1350,885,911]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="socialis">Chrysobothris socialis</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1366,1426,885,911]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Type</typeStatus>
) Waterh.” Ventanas is in Durango (
<bibRefCitation author="Selander" box="[553,851,925,951]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" refString="Selander, R. B. &amp; Vaurie, P. (1962) A gazetteer to accompany the Insecta volumes of the Biologa Centrali-Americana. American Museum Novitates, 2099, 1 - 70." type="journal article" year="1962">
Selander &amp; Vaurie, 
<number box="[788,851,925,951]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="1962.0">1962</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The frons is entirely coppery, the occiput green. There is a vague median longitudinal depression extending from behind the clypeus to about mid-point. The sides of the pronotum are narrowly, yet boldly, coppery-red except near the base. The ventral surface is coppery bronze.
</paragraph>
